            <FONT FACE="arial,helvetica,sans-serif" COLOR="#CC0000" SIZE="5"><B>Asia Buzz: Virus Alert</B><BR>
            </FONT> <FONT FACE="arial,helvetica,sans-serif" COLOR="#666666" SIZE="3"><B>Do not read this article!</B><BR>
            </FONT> <FONT FACE="arial,helvetica,sans-serif" COLOR="#333333" SIZE="2">By ADI IGNATIUS<BR>
            </FONT><BR>
            <FONT FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333333"><I><B>May 
            8, 2000 </B><BR>
            Web posted at 3 p.m. Hong Kong time, 3 a.m. EDT</I><BR>
            </FONT><BR>
            <FONT FACE="arial,helvetica,sans-serif" COLOR="#333333" SIZE="2">




It's the most remarkable Philippine export since Marcos took all the money from the treasury. A young Filipino hacker devised a computer bug that spread around the world last week, jamming electronic communications and paralyzing entire corporations. The virus introduced itself with a deceptively enticing message: I Love You.
            <BR>
